T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 392
EP  - 402
VL  - 7
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A specific communication methodology for the study of organizational behavior at the level of the interpersonal relationship it presented. The model for analysis uses the transaction, patterned as probabilistic recurring sequences, as the basic unit of analysis and analyzes these stochastic processes using a Markovian framework. Exemplary applications of the methodology are presented, with discussion of methods to identify differences in interaction patterns both within a group and across groups.
AB  - A specific communication methodology for the study of organizational behavior at the level of the interpersonal relationship it presented. The model for analysis uses the transaction, patterned as probabilistic recurring sequences, as the basic unit of analysis and analyzes these stochastic processes using a Markovian framework. Exemplary applications of the methodology are presented, with discussion of methods to identify differences in interaction patterns both within a group and across groups.
